The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Delleker had a population of 802. The population density was {{convert|289.9|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Delleker was 568 (70.8%) [[White Americans|White]], 2 (0.2%) [[African Americans|African American]], 30 (3.7%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 8 (1.0%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 104 (13.0%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 90 (11.2%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 236 persons (29.4%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Delleker CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0618485 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 19, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 296 households, out of which 89 (30.1%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 134 (45.3%) were married-couple households, 18 (6.1%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 78 (26.4%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 66 (22.3%) had a male householder with no partner present. 109 households (36.8%) were one person, and 55 (18.6%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.71.<ref name=DP1/> There were 169 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (57.1% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Delleker CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0618485 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 19, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 221 people (27.6%) under the age of 18, 55 people (6.9%) aged 18 to 24, 196 people (24.4%) aged 25 to 44, 199 people (24.8%) aged 45 to 64, and 131 people (16.3%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 38.0{{nbsp}}years.    For every 100 females, there were 95.6 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 339 housing units at an average density of {{convert|122.6|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 296 (87.3%) were occupied. Of these, 190 (64.2%) were owner-occupied, and 106 (35.8%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

